<Docs title="Security Signals" description="How Dep Beacon uses OSV.dev vulnerability data.">
  <h1>Security Signals</h1>
  <p>
    Dep Beacon can query OSV.dev for the package and version currently selected by a range. The result is summarized without replacing a full audit workflow.
  </p>

  <h2>Severity mapping</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Low and medium advisories show as orange warning signals.</li>
    <li>High and critical advisories show as red error signals.</li>
    <li>Unknown severity stays visible as known risk.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Privacy and control</h2>
  <p>
    Disable OSV checks with `depBeacon.checkVulnerabilities` when working offline or inside registries that should not send dependency names to external services.
  </p>

  <pre><code>{disableOsvExample}</code></pre>
</Docs>
